features: Separate Shoe Compartment: The gym backpack is equipped with a dedicated shoe compartment, enabling you to store your shoes or other sports accessories separately from the rest of your belongings. This compartment can also function as a regular pocket for your daily use.

Large Capacity: The WANDF drawstring gym bag measures 19 x 18 inches, providing ample space to hold your sports gear or daily essentials. Inside the main compartment, you'll find 1 interior wall zip pocket and 2 interior wall pockets, allowing for perfect classification of your items.

Organized Multi-Pockets: The string backpack includes a concealed back pocket designed to keep your cell phone and wallet secure. Additionally, a front zipper pocket offers easy access to keys or ID cards, eliminating the need for digging. The two side mesh pockets are ideal for keeping cold water bottles or wet umbrellas separate from your other belongings.

Design Details: This cinch sack is crafted from tear-resistant and water-resistant fabric. The widened straps effectively alleviate stress on your shoulders and can be easily adjusted to your desired length. Furthermore, the gym drawstring backpack comes with a hanging loop for convenient storage.

Multi-Use: This drawstring bag is capable of accommodating all your essential active gear, such as basketballs, soccer balls, baseball gloves, volleyballs, and more. It also serves as a versatile daily bag for activities like going to the library, shopping, training, and hiking.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 20, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Much Better Bag Than I Expected
reviews.reviewText: Needed an over the shoulder bag to act as a lightweight briefcase for transporting work items (mostly folders with occasional books), but didn't want a full backpack. This bag is working very well. It's big enough for folders and textbooks (even my laptop) with room to spare. The interior pockets are great for pens, whiteboard markers, a snack bar, etc. and the outside zipper pocket is a bonus. I don't use the shoe compartments. The mesh pouches on the side too small for a large water bottle, but hold an umbrella perfectly. I usually carry the bag over one shoulder but, if carrying books, I sometimes use both straps like a backpack. Even though the straps aren't padded, they are reasonably comfortable. Would definitely be fine if carrying lighter weight items. The drawstring closure is fairly tight given the width of the straps. There is also a loop for hanging. The entire bag is lined. The fabric seems sturdy and shows no sign of wear after 8 weeks of daily use. It states that it is water resistant, but I gave it an extra spray of waterproofing just to be safe. Have carried it in light rain and everything has stayed dry. Overall, it's a much better bag than I expected and suits my needs well. It would be good for travel as a carry on or day pack. And no, I did not receive any form of compensation for this review. It's just a good bag.

reviews.reviewText: The media could not be loaded. I'm in love with this backpack. I love the fact that it doent look bulky when you tie it close. The bag is very flexible. Meaning you can fit a lot of stuff in the bag. Most backpacks have a tighter structure to the bag. So it's limited to how much stuff you can put in the bag. If you get a chance to purchase it, you'll see what I mean. This is the best backpack I've ever owned. I realized that in the first 5mins. Especially after I opened the bag and saw how wide and deep the bag is. You really cant tell that the bag opens up that wide by looking at it on the outside. It has so much room and is very flexible. It looks like it does well in the rain as well. I'm quite sure it's rain proof. 20$ is a steal for this bag. This bag is more like a 50$-60$ quality backpack for sure. I'm so happy with this backpack . I mite get a few other ones in different color. I highly highly recommend buying this backpack in any color to your likingThank you again AMAZON

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 31, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars It's nice, bigger than I thought
reviews.reviewText: Bought this for my kid for school because it looked relatively rugged. It seems to be holding up to middle school pretty well, and he likes it. The large pocket is lined in plastic like it's water resistant, but the side pocket is not. I kinda wish it was opposite, as he puts his books in the big pocket and his water bottle in the side pocket. The bag itself is way bigger than I thought it would be, and I like that the straps are wide so they don't cut into the shoulders. I'd buy it again!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 18, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Sturdy, thick material
reviews.reviewText: I was pleasantly surprised as how sturdy this bag is. It almost feels like it's insulated. I poured some water on it to test the water resistance and the inside stayed nice and dry. The straps are much more comfortable than the cheaper bags with the rope ties and it has more zippered pockets than I expected - one outside on the front and another small zippered pouch inside as well. I plan to use this bag for trips to theme parks and I think it's going to be perfect. I'd definitely recommend this bag to anyone looking for a sturdier, more protective bag for things like sweatshirts, towels, etc.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 25, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Exceeded my expectations for this price point. It’s very sturdy!
reviews.reviewText: I ordered this for a seashell tour in FL and had limited expectations of this, given the price. It was heavier and overall larger than expected, but I didn’t have time to return so I took it on my trip. It ended up exceeding my expectations! I had pounds of seashells, water boots, water bottle, my jacket, and Fanny pack in this thing and it held up. Definitely not as flimsy as expected. The light blue color is really pretty as well.
